.TH "tty_ldisc_receive_buf" 9 "tty_ldisc_receive_buf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_ldisc_receive_buf \- forward data to line discipline
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tty_ldisc_receive_buf
.BI "(struct tty_ldisc *ld "  ","
.BI "const unsigned char *p "  ","
.BI "char *f "  ","
.BI "int count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ld" 12
line discipline to process input
.IP "p" 12
char buffer
.IP "f" 12
TTY_* flags buffer
.IP "count" 12
number of bytes to process

Callers other than \fBflush_to_ldisc\fP need to exclude the kworker
from concurrent use of the line discipline, see \fBpaste_selection\fP.

Returns the number of bytes processed
